org.joda.primitives.collection.impl

Class ArrayFloatCollection

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.joda.primitives.collection.impl.AbstractPrimitiveCollectable<java.lang.Float>
      • org.joda.primitives.collection.impl.AbstractFloatCollection
        • org.joda.primitives.collection.impl.ArrayFloatCollection
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.Float>, java.util.Collection<java.lang.Float>, FloatCollection, PrimitiveCollection<java.lang.Float>, FloatIterable, PrimitiveCollectable<java.lang.Float>

    public class ArrayFloatCollection
extends AbstractFloatCollection
implements java.lang.Cloneable
    Array based implementation of FloatCollection for primitive float elements.

    This collection implementation allows multiple copies of the same value to be added. Internally, it uses an array, and behaves much like a list.

    This class implements Collection allowing seamless integration with other APIs.

    Add, Remove and Clear are supported.

    Since:
    1.0
